 class=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"report-settings" data-id=
=3D"hat_report-settings"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"report-=
settings" data-id=3D"report-settings">Report settings</h2><a class=3D"absol=
ute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"report-settings" data-id=3D"hab_report-settings"=
></a><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">You can adjust the following to customiz=
e your report.</p><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start=
"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Add data to your report</p></li><li class=3D"it=
ems-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Customize column display names</p></li=
><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Adjust the report time=
 frame</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Apply fi=
lters to include and exclude information</p></li><li class=3D"items-start">=
<p class=3D"font-normal ">Change the way the data is joined</p></li><li cla=
ss=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Group the rows in your report<=
/p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Aggregate the d=
ata in your report</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-norma=
l ">Add a pivot table</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-no=
rmal ">Chart your report data</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D=
"font-normal ">Select the target currency for your report</p></li></ul><br>=
<h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"add-data-to-your-report" data-id=3D"=
add-data-to-your-report">Add data to your report</h3><br><p class=3D"font-n=
ormal ">The first step when building a report is to add the data fields you=
 want to include using the data selector panel on the left. Each field you =
add will appear as a column in the report.</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md b=
order border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"DataSelectorPanel" src=3D"https://imag=
es.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/2u3Xcm8nrAcQftaxqtHOiK/dcc862ee2748a849badb06=
fed2577cb8/DataSelectorPanel.png"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Learn more =
in <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"http=
s://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D2YT4LSf4WTJoMrNOkicFyd">our artic=
le about the reports data selector</a>.</p><br><div class=3D"my-2 border bo=
rder-solid rounded-md p-4 md:py-4 md:grid md:grid-cols-10  border-[#D3DBEC]=
 bg-[#F6F8FB]  "><div class=3D"hidden md:col-span-1 md:flex justify-center"=
> <img class=3D"h-6" src=3D"https://static-assets.ripplingcdn.com/bizsys/hc=
_functional-icons/noteIcons/hc_information.png" alt=3D"Information"> </div>=
<div class=3D"md:col-span-9"><p class=3D"font-normal text-gray-700"></p><p =
class=3D"font-normal ">When you include fields from 3 or more objects or ad=
d a Report Formula to your report, it qualifies as an Advanced Report, whic=
h is a feature tied to your Rippling Platform tier. For more information, s=
ee&nbsp;<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D=
"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D143641281607">our article ab=
out what qualifies as an Advanced Report</a>.</p><p></p></div></div><br><h3=
 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"customize-column-display-names" data-id=
=3D"customize-column-display-names">Customize column display names</h3><br>=
<p class=3D"font-normal ">You can apply a custom display name to each colum=
n in the report. To add a custom display name:</p><br><ol class=3D" list-[d=
ecimal]  pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">On the D=
ata panel, locate the field.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"=
font-normal ">Click the three dots next to the field name.</p></li><li clas=
s=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Add your preferred display name=
 in the <b>Column Display Name</b> field.
</p><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"Reports-C=
ustomDisplayName" src=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/5arKGbaX=
8Urk8k5usPGLSk/00e7302ab5948cfd2fbd0b963526e91f/Screenshot_2025-09-23_at_4.=
10.30%C3%A2__PM.png"></li></ol><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">The display na=
me is immediately updated in the report. If you ever want to revert back to=
 the default field name, just remove the text from the <b>Column Display Na=
me</b> field.</p><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"adjust-the-repo=
rt-time-frame" data-id=3D"adjust-the-report-time-frame">Adjust the report t=
ime frame</h3><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">One of the most important eleme=
nts of your report is the time frame over which you're analyzing data.</p><=
br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Reports have one of two types of time frames:<=
/p><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"f=
ont-normal "><b>Snapshot</b>. These reports show the values for a single da=
y, and default to the current date. You can select another single date.</p>=
</li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Range of time</=
b>. These reports show values over a range of time defined by a start and e=
nd date, and default to the last three months. You can modify this to cover=
 any period of time.</p></li></ul><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Learn more =
in our article about&nbsp;<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:curso=
r-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D9630976624=
66">changing the time frame in a report</a>.</p><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl f=
ont-bold" id=3D"apply-filters-to-include-and-exclude-information" data-id=
=3D"apply-filters-to-include-and-exclude-information">Apply filters to incl=
ude and exclude information</h3><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">When you need=
 to pare down the data in your report, you can add filters. To add a filter=
, click&nbsp;<b>Add filter +</b> in the Filters panel.</p><br><img class=3D=
"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"ReportFilters" src=3D"http=
s://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/5jnlmITdSKpEyeiSNfaMDB/e88d0bb607c8e3=
35ed0290f0e81ba766/ReportFilters.png"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">In most=
 reports, there are two types of filters: <b>Employee</b> filters&nbsp;and =
<b>Column</b> filters. Employee filters let you filter the report using cur=
rent information about your employees, and column filters let you filter th=
e report using the data in the columns and rows of the report. Learn more i=
n <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https=
://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D954086222134">our article about re=
port filters</a>.</p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">By default, reports are =
filtered to include just employees who are currently active. You can change=
 this if you want to include employees with different statuses.</p><br><h3 =
class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"change-the-way-data-is-joined" data-id=
=3D"change-the-way-data-is-joined">Change the way data is joined</h3><br><p=
 class=3D"font-normal ">If your report uses data from multiple datasets, yo=
u may want to change the way it=E2=80=99s joined. For example, you could ch=
ange the join from a <b>left</b> join to an <b>inner</b> join to limit the =
dataset to only employees with values in both datasets.</p><br><img class=
=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"EditJoins" src=3D"https=
://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/2aVxrYxY9ELLPFhlk80H5R/94cf9169506b1ec=
a26804b1fee05fa28/EditJoins.png"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">To learn mor=
e about the types of joins, see&nbsp;<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 =
hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=
=3D20567317535">our article about data joins</a>. To learn how to update th=
e joins, see <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" hr=
ef=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D617200643900">our artic=
le about how to change joints in a report</a>. </p><br><p class=3D"font-nor=
mal ">The ability to change how the data is joined is available in most rep=
orts, but not available in a select set of report recipes.</p><br><h3 class=
=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"group-the-rows-in-your-report" data-id=3D"gro=
up-the-rows-in-your-report">Group the rows in your report</h3><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">If you want to consolidate the data in your report, you c=
an group it using any of the fields in the report. For example, you could g=
roup by employee or department to group related rows together and show a si=
ngle column for each category.</p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">To group th=
e report, drag and drop fields from the <b>Columns</b> area into the <b>Row=
 Grouping</b> area.</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25=
 my-4" alt=3D"RowGrouping" src=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3=
/0mR2BxAqAZiO1NnOW2prF/018e46ad06e6a506ae82f1c3449b5baa/RowGrouping.png"><b=
r><p class=3D"font-normal ">Learn more in <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue=
-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articl=
eId=3D3uYjASEUR46DorZ4uo0YoP">our article about grouping and aggregating re=
port data</a>.</p><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"aggregate-the-=
data-in-your-report" data-id=3D"aggregate-the-data-in-your-report">Aggregat=
e the data in your report</h3><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Once you've gro=
uped your rows of data, you can choose to aggregate the data by calculating=
 a value such as a sum, average, minimum, or maximum.&nbsp;</p><br><img cla=
ss=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"Aggregation" src=3D"h=
ttps://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/1lMWDolwRUjnSvhMSoEjO9/ad1419956aa=
d3ff60db8eab9ca3691b2/Aggregation.png"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Learn =
more in <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D=
"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D3uYjASEUR46DorZ4uo0YoP">our =
article about grouping and aggregating report data</a>.</p><br><h3 class=3D=
"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"add-a-pivot-table" data-id=3D"add-a-pivot-table"=
>Add a pivot table</h3><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">If you want to add mul=
tiple groupings or compare multiple data points in a report, you may want t=
o add a pivot table.</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-2=
5 my-4" alt=3D"Pivot" src=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/5VWe=
eRWoKgi2ULg5ZGlUXi/3e74c45bc7196fca1a253ec8c24b5a0d/Pivot.png"><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">Pivot tables present data in a tabular format so you can =
compare values side-by-side. They=E2=80=99re great for quickly spotting tre=
nds and seeing anomalies. For example, if you want to see patterns in turno=
ver based on employee tenure for each location, department, and manager, yo=
ur best option for presenting the data will be a pivot table.</p><br><p cla=
ss=3D"font-normal ">Learn more in <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hov=
er:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D70=
7600994149">our article about how to build pivot tables</a>.</p><br><h3 cla=
ss=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"chart-your-report-data" data-id=3D"chart-yo=
ur-report-data">Chart your report data</h3><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">On=
ce you've run your report, if you're analyzing data using grouping and aggr=
egation, you have the option to add some visualizations. Click the <b>Chart=
s</b> button at the top of your report to generate a chart.</p><br><img cla=
ss=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"Charts" src=3D"https:=
//images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/4Mjvc8CXM6ynRZjSbPHfZV/d4113bab7767f905=
f5b7b12a38630072/Charts.png"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">You can change t=
he chart type and other settings to customize your chart. For more informat=
ion, see&nbsp;<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" h=
ref=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D30027949316">our artic=
le about charts</a>.</p><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"select-t=
he-target-currency-for-your-report" data-id=3D"select-the-target-currency-f=
or-your-report">Select the target currency for your report</h3><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">If your report contains monetary values, you can convert =
them to any currency supported by Rippling.&nbsp;To do so, select the desir=
ed currency in the top right corner of the report.</p><br><img class=3D"sha=
dow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"ReportTargetCurrency" src=3D"h=
ttps://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/47QUo2IcrevdMpTarpNu8K/f830ce3b0b2=
7570b00385cd4d68488b7/ReportTargetCurrency.png"><br><p class=3D"font-normal=
 ">Learn more about<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-point=
er" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D972194299658"> ho=
w currency conversion&nbsp;works in reports</a>.</p><br><a class=3D"absolut=
e opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"share-and-download-reports" data-id=3D"hat_=
share-and-download-reports"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"shar=
e-and-download-reports" data-id=3D"share-and-download-reports">Share and do=
wnload reports</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"share-and-do=
wnload-reports" data-id=3D"hab_share-and-download-reports"></a><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">Once you create a report, you can save it for future use,=
 share it with your colleagues within Rippling, and download it for offline=
 reference.</p><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><=
p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Share</b>: Sharing a report lets your colleague=
s access report data in real-time, meaning any changes you make to the repo=
rt automatically flow through to shared recipients. Shared reports give rec=
ipients access to "evergreen" data, no matter when the recipient looks at t=
he report. Note that you can lock columns or an entire report before you sh=
are it so recipients can see the latest data but cannot edit the report. Le=
arn more in&nbsp;<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer=
" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D360056300973">our a=
rticle about sharing reports</a>.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p clas=
s=3D"font-normal "><b>Download</b>: If you need your report in CSV or Excel=
 format, you can download the report. This is useful if you want to save a =
snapshot of the report at download time, but if you want to share a report =
with colleagues and ensure that they're always seeing the latest data, your=
 best bet is to use the <b>share</b> option. For additional details, see&nb=
sp;<a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"http=
s://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D197466294837">our article about h=
ow report data looks when downloaded</a>.</p></li></ul><br><a class=3D"abso=
lute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"special-report-recipes-with-limited-capa=
bilities" data-id=3D"hat_special-report-recipes-with-limited-capabilities">=
</a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"special-report-recipes-with-limi=
ted-capabilities" data-id=3D"special-report-recipes-with-limited-capabiliti=
es">Special report recipes with limited capabilities</h2><a class=3D"absolu=
te mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"special-report-recipes-with-limited-capabilities"=
 data-id=3D"hab_special-report-recipes-with-limited-capabilities"></a><br><=
p class=3D"font-normal ">There are a few special report recipes in Rippling=
 that do not have the same full set of capabilities as most reports:</p><br=
><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-no=
rmal ">Headcount report (previous version)</p></li><li class=3D"items-start=
"><p class=3D"font-normal ">PEO insurance billing report</p></li><li class=
=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Talent retention rate</p></li><l=
i class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Time &amp; Attendance cha=
nge history report</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-norma=
l ">Workflow Studio triggered events report</p></li><li class=3D"items-star=
t"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Workflow Studio triggered actions report</p></=
li></ul><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">When you use these recipes, your opti=
ons for customizing the report may be limited.</p><br></div></div><!----></=
